OL,6,F"However, parents will likely be
OL,7,Fsurprised that at a time when schools
OL,8,Fare struggling to find enough teachers
OL,9,Fto teach classes, when buildings are
OL,10,Fcrumbling, and when we are in the
OL,11,Fmiddle of a crisis in special needs
OL,12,Fprovision, that the Government is
OL,13,Fchoosing to focus on increasing fines
OL,14,Ffor parents.
OL,16,F"Good attendance is obviously
OL,17,Fcritically important, but fines have
OL,18,Flong proven to be too blunt a tool and
OL,19,Flargely ineffective at improving
OL,20,Fpersistent absence."
OL,26,@nD@AOUxD@AOU|D@TO]
