OL,6,F"Not only does it affect the child's
OL,7,Feducation but it means teachers then
OL,8,Fhave to spend time helping children to
OL,9,Fcatch-up with lost learning. If
OL,10,Feverybody did this it would be chaos."
OL,12,FLabour's shadow education secretary
OL,13,FBridget Phillipson said: "The
OL,14,FConservatives are only just waking up
OL,15,Fto the damage of persistent absence
OL,16,Fthat has reached historic levels on
OL,17,Ftheir watch, but their answer
OL,18,Faddresses the symptoms of absence, not
OL,19,Fthe causes.
