OL,6,F"Persistent absence was rising long
OL,7,Fbefore the pandemic ` the result of
OL,8,Fgrowing unaddressed mental ill health
OL,9,Fand the impact of years of economic
OL,10,Fdecline hitting family finances and a
OL,11,Fbreakdown of trust between schools and
OL,12,Ffamilies.
OL,14,F"The Tories should follow Labour's
OL,15,Fplan to tackle absence, introduce a
OL,16,Fregister of children not in school,
OL,17,Fbringing together children's existing
OL,18,Frecords and investing in access to
OL,19,Fmental health counselling support in
OL,20,Fevery school to deal with persistent
OL,21,Fabsence once and for all."
